<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1437,691,1221]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Karyotype: 2n = 62 and FN = 64. Autosomal complement: two biarmed pairs medium to small size, and 28 acrocentric pairs (one very large and the remaining large to small decreasing in size). Sex chromosomes: X chromosome presented two different morphologies, a large subtelocentric, and a large acrocentric; Y, a small acrocentric (Myer &amp; Carleton 1981; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Weksler, M." box="[429,737,835,861]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="90 - 103" refId="ref64575" refString="Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Weksler, M. (1998) A new species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) from northeastern and central Brazil. Zeitschrift fur Saugetierkunde, 63, 90 - 103." type="journal article" year="1998">Bonvicino &amp; Weksler 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Andrades-Miranda, J. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Lima-Rosa, C. A. &amp; Nunes, A. P. &amp; Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S." box="[747,1098,835,861]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1080 - 1091" refId="ref63690" refString="Andrades-Miranda, J., Oliveira, L. F. B., Lima-Rosa, C. A., Nunes, A. P., Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. (2001 a) Chromosome studies of seven species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia: Sigmodontinae) from Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy, 82, 1080 - 1091. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 1545 - 1542 (2001) 082 % 3 C 1080: CSOSSO % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Andrades-Miranda 
<emphasis box="[965,1013,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2001a
</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 1084, 
<figureCitation box="[1220,1306,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1191,1215]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,281,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-69@7.[151,1436,273,1168]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Cerradomys. (□) C. akroai; (■) C. goytaca; (ê) C. langguthi; (r) C. maracajuensis; (▲) C. marinhus; (○) C. scotti; (☆) C. subflavus; (l) C. vivoi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423619/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Weksler, M. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R." pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="113 - 130" refId="ref75594" refString="Weksler, M. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. (2005) Taxonomy of pigmy rice rats genus Oligoryzomys Bangs, 1900 (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) of the Brazilian cerrado, with the description of two new species. Arquivos do Museu Nacional, 63, 113 - 130." type="journal article" year="2005">Weksler &amp; Bonvicino 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pereira, L. G. &amp; Geise, L." box="[346,591,871,897]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="509 - 518" refId="ref71824" refString="Pereira, L. G. &amp; Geise, L. (2007) Karyotype composition of some rodents and marsupials from Chapada Diamantina (Bahia, Brasil). Brazilian Journal of Biology, 67 (3), 509 - 518. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1519 - 69842007000300016" type="journal article" year="2007">Pereira &amp; Geise 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Ventura, K. &amp; Ferguson-Smith, M. A. &amp; O'Brien, P. C. M. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[603,824,870,897]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="0117579" refId="ref66405" refString="Di-Nizo, C. B., Ventura, K., Ferguson-Smith, M. A., O'Brien, P. C. M., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2015) Comparative chromosome painting in six species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) and the karyotype evolution of the genus. Public Library of Science one, 10 (2), e 0117579. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0117579" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di-Nizo 
<emphasis box="[702,751,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Weksler, M. &amp; Lemos, E. M. S. &amp; D'Andrea, P. S. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R." box="[835,1058,871,897]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref76087" refString="Weksler, M., Lemos, E. M. S., D'Andrea, P. S. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. (2017) The taxonomic status of Oligoryzomys mattogrossae (Allen 1916) (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae), reservoir of Anajatuba Hantavirus. American Museum Novitates, 3880, 1 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 3880.1" type="journal article" year="2017">
Weksler 
<emphasis box="[934,983,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). A different fundamental number of 66 was reported due to the presence of one small metacentric pair instead of an acrocentric one, moreover, this karyotype also presented a submetacentric Y chromosome (
<bibRefCitation author="Andrades-Miranda, J. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Lima-Rosa, C. A. &amp; Nunes, A. P. &amp; Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S." box="[820,1177,943,969]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1080 - 1091" refId="ref63690" refString="Andrades-Miranda, J., Oliveira, L. F. B., Lima-Rosa, C. A., Nunes, A. P., Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. (2001 a) Chromosome studies of seven species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia: Sigmodontinae) from Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy, 82, 1080 - 1091. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 1545 - 1542 (2001) 082 % 3 C 1080: CSOSSO % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Andrades-Miranda 
<emphasis box="[1041,1090,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2001a
</bibRefCitation>
). This variation in fundamental number occurs sympatrically on specimens collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[877,945,979,1005]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, state of 
<collectingCountry box="[1041,1109,979,1005]" name="Brazil" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation box="[1122,1208,979,1005]" captionStart="TABLE 9" captionStartId="62.[151,239,502,528]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="TABLE 9. Karyotype data of genus Oligoryzomys. Species, diploid (2n) and fundamental (FN) numbers, collection localities, geographic coordinates and reference." pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Table 9</tableCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1218,1299,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1098,1122]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,187,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-17@59.[151,1436,181,1073]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 17. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Oligoryzomys. (r) O. mattogrossae; (■) O. microtis; (○) O. moojeni; (☆) O. rupestris; (▲) O. stramineus; (l) O. utiaritensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423661/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). C-banding metaphases exhibited blocks of constitutive heterochromatin on the pericentromeric region of all autosomes, with the exception of the large acrocentric pair. The X chromosome presented pericentromeric heterochromatic blocks varied in size. The Y chromosome was entirely heterochromatic (
<bibRefCitation author="Andrades-Miranda, J. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Lima-Rosa, C. A. &amp; Nunes, A. P. &amp; Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S." box="[887,1246,1087,1113]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1080 - 1091" refId="ref63690" refString="Andrades-Miranda, J., Oliveira, L. F. B., Lima-Rosa, C. A., Nunes, A. P., Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. (2001 a) Chromosome studies of seven species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia: Sigmodontinae) from Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy, 82, 1080 - 1091. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 1545 - 1542 (2001) 082 % 3 C 1080: CSOSSO % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Andrades-Miranda 
<emphasis box="[1108,1158,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2001a
</bibRefCitation>
). G-banding was also performed (
<bibRefCitation author="Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Ventura, K. &amp; Ferguson-Smith, M. A. &amp; O'Brien, P. C. M. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[335,560,1122,1149]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="0117579" refId="ref66405" refString="Di-Nizo, C. B., Ventura, K., Ferguson-Smith, M. A., O'Brien, P. C. M., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2015) Comparative chromosome painting in six species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) and the karyotype evolution of the genus. Public Library of Science one, 10 (2), e 0117579. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0117579" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di-Nizo 
<emphasis box="[435,485,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). Multiple NORs, were localized on the short arms of one to three pairs. FISH with telomeric sequences revealed signals exclusively at the ends of all chromosome arms and no interstitial signals were observed (
<bibRefCitation author="Andrades-Miranda, J. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Lima-Rosa, C. A. &amp; Nunes, A. P. &amp; Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S." box="[328,684,1195,1221]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1080 - 1091" refId="ref63690" refString="Andrades-Miranda, J., Oliveira, L. F. B., Lima-Rosa, C. A., Nunes, A. P., Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. (2001 a) Chromosome studies of seven species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia: Sigmodontinae) from Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy, 82, 1080 - 1091. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 1545 - 1542 (2001) 082 % 3 C 1080: CSOSSO % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Andrades-Miranda 
<emphasis box="[548,598,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2001a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
